main event: Multiple unidentified metallic objects displaying erratic flight patterns, high/low speeds, and hovering were detected by both ground and air intercept radar in the Aleutian Islands on May 8, 1962.
interesting points: The radar contacts and visual sightings were of many metallic objects, the exact nature and origin of which were unknown.
The objects were observed performing maneuvers at high and low speeds, including hovering.
The Air Force investigation concluded that the radar contacts and visual sightings were caused by the unidentified metallic objects, but their exact nature and origin remained unknown.
The report includes photographs of the objects, though the image provided does not actually contain any photographs.
The sighting lasted for an unspecified duration, but the report mentions that the objects were visually held for 16 minutes.
sighted object: multiple metallic objects performing erratic maneuvers
